<node TEXT="rot cipher" ID="ID_481187391" CREATED="1674312411795" MODIFIED="1674312769939" LINK="https://www.dcode.fr/rot-cipher"><richcontent TYPE="NOTE" CONTENT-TYPE="xml/">
<html>
  <head>
    
  </head>
  <body>
    <div http-equiv="content-type" content="text/html; charset=utf-8" itemprop="acceptedAnswer" itemscope="" itemtype="http://schema.org/Answer">
      <div itemprop="text">
        <p>
          Rot-N/Rot cipher (for Rotation) is a simple character substitution based on a shift/rotation of N letters in an alphabet. E.g. one letter is replaced by another (always the same) that is located further (exactly N letters further) in the alphabet.
        </p>
        <p>
          This is the basis of the famous <a href="https://www.dcode.fr/caesar-cipher">Caesar code</a>&nbsp;and its many variants modifying the shift. The most popular variant is the <a href="https://www.dcode.fr/rot-13-cipher">ROT13</a>&nbsp;which has the advantage of being reversible with our 26 letters alphabet (the encryption or decryption operations are identical because 13 is half of 26).
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </body>
