<node TEXT="RELRO" ID="ID_16569347" CREATED="1679782175402" MODIFIED="1696009549407" LINK="https://ctf101.org/binary-exploitation/relocation-read-only/"><richcontent TYPE="NOTE" CONTENT-TYPE="xml/">
<html>
  <head>
    
  </head>
  <body>
    <p>
      Relocation Read-Only (or RELRO) is a security measure which makes some binary sections read-only. There are two RELRO &quot;modes&quot;: partial and full.
    </p>
    <p>
      Partial RELRO is good news, full RELRO is bad news
