      pwn template ./vuln --host 182.123.1.23 --port 3412 &gt; exploit.py
    </p>
    <p>
      
    </p>
    <p>
      it creates an exploit that can be run locally or remotely:
    </p>
    <p>
      - Local run: python3 exploit.py LOCAL
    </p>
    <p>
      - To the host specified: python3 exploit.py
    </p>
    <p>
      
    </p>
    <p>
      Interesting commands for the exploit.py (after <b>io=start()</b>):
    </p>
    <p>
      io.recvuntil(&quot;&lt;TEXTSTRING&gt;&quot;)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;e.g. io.recvuntil(&quot;input your choice:&quot;)
    </p>
    <p>
      io.recvline(&lt;True/False&gt;) with false it does not include the new line
    </p>
    <p>
      io.send(&quot;&lt;TEXTSTRING&gt;&quot;)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;e.g. io.send(&quot;1&quot;)
    </p>
    <p>
      io.sendline(&quot;&lt;TEXTSTRING&gt;&quot;) it sends the /n at the end of the string e.g. io.sendline(&quot;A&quot;*136 + &quot;\x87\x40\x36\x10\x00\x00&quot;) it sends 136 As starting in the address 000010364087 (you might have been able to get the address with nm)
    </p>
