<node TEXT="32 bits vs 64 bits" ID="ID_608231622" CREATED="1681403278923" MODIFIED="1681583191394"><richcontent TYPE="NOTE" CONTENT-TYPE="xml/">
<html>
  <head>
    
  </head>
  <body>
    <p>
      registers in 32 bit architecture start with e
    </p>
    <p>
      registers in 64 bit architecture start with r
    </p>
    <p>
      IMPORTANT FOR 64 bits!!!: the rip (register for instruction pointer) in 64 bits will only accept canonical addresses (a canonical address is between 0x000000000000&nbsp;&nbsp;- 0x0000007FFFFFFFFF and another upper chunk, however, the space in between is not canonical and will never overwrite the rip).
    </p>
  </body>
</html></richcontent>
